See Also
Foot & mouth disease - UK 20010220.0325
Foot & mouth disease - UK (16) 20010304.0438
[1
Date: 5 Mar 2001
From: ProMed-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: BBC, 5 Mar 2001 [edited
<http://news.bbc.co.uk/hi/english/uk/newsid_1190000/1190408.stm>

The official number of confirmed FMD cases across the UK stands at 72 at
1700GMT on Monday [5 Mar 2001.
On Sunday 2 new cases were confirmed at sites near Burnside farm,
Heddon-on-the-Wall, Northumberland, which is believed to be the source of
the outbreak.
An outbreak has been confirmed among cattle at Prestwick Hall Farm in
Ponteland, Northumberland, only 4 miles away from Heddon-on-the-Wall. It
means 100 cows and 300 sheep will have to be incinerated.
An outbreak was confirmed on Monday at a farm in Westerhope,
Northumberland. A 5-mile exclusion zone has been imposed.
In County Durham 5 cases of FMD have now been confirmed. Other outbreaks
have also been confirmed at a pig farm in Hamsterley; an abattoir in Witton
le Wear; a sheep farm in Dinnington, Tyne and Wear; a pig and cattle farm
at Throckley, Tyne and Wear; a sheep farm in Throckley; a farm in
Wolsington; a cattle farm in St Weonards in Herefordshire on Saturday; a
sheep farm in Stonesby near Melton Mowbray; and Lindley Hall farm in Fenny
Drayton near Hinckley, both in Leicestershire.
Another suspected case has been found on a farm near Newnham on Severn, on
the outskirts of the Forest of Dean. A restricted area has been imposed in
the Forest south of the A40 and west of the A48.
At an abattoir at Gaerwen on Anglesey, north Wales, 3 cases have been
confirmed. Farms at Painscastle near Hay-on-Wye and Felindre near Newtown
were also hit. The first case in Oxfordshire, at a sheep farm at Little
Chesterton, was confirmed on Saturday.
An outbreak of the disease has been confirmed at the Blue House farm at
North Fambridge, Essex. The farm, owned by the Essex Wildlife Trust, is
situated on the northern banks of the River Crouch. The first case of
foot-and-mouth in Cornwall was confirmed on Saturday at an abattoir in
South Petherwin, near Launceston.
Sunday saw a second case confirmed at a mixed livestock farm at Lezant.
There is a suspected case in Charlton, near Malmesbury, Wiltshire and
another near the border with Berkshire at Bishopstone.
